And I regret it soooo much, that I ever attempted to get it started.<br>
<br>
When I went lvl 24 I was so happy that I can have Everfount and Corncucopia finally.<br>
<br>
So first I attempted to start the practise research. Wasted a few fruitless hours on it before I gave up. Then I pumped money into the research skill and got it to 46.<br>
I thought that would be a good time to try it and I was hoping to get at least 1 of the both spells with the 3 Words of Transcendence I had.<br>
<br>
what shall i say...failed all three times.<br>
Just for the fun of it I tried to research the lvl 24 Pets for which I had 2 scrolls available.<br>
Failed again both times.<br>
<br>
Now I think it's complete bull**** and after that I didn't play my mage for almost 2 months and started a druid up ;-)<br>
<br>
I mean a random factor is nice, but when my skill is 46, shouldn't I have gotten at least *1* spell out of the 5 attempts?<br>
<br>
and sure, many of you just say &quot;I will just buy the skill&quot;.<br>
But for somebody who doesn't have a high-lvl-main for the money supply and who also cannot play the game for 10 hours a day to get all the components I think that's ridiculous.<br>
<br>
Oh well...started to play the Mage again a bit.<br>
Lived up to 29 with the earth Pet only. wasting time to summon food and drink whenever I log in. (poor people like me have to save coins where they can ;-) ). and for the levels 29-33 I won't need more than my Fire Pet as it seems ;-)<br>
<br>
But still I know it will suck at higher levels not to have all teh Pets available.<br>
And maybe I'm just unlucky but from 24 to 28 I got hundreds of Words from all the Mobs I fought. But not a single one for the Mage class.<br>
<br>
Sorry, it's not very constructive, I just think the whole research stinks big time ;-)<br>
